This machine came into the Shop for a hydraulic leak. I was doing my walk around inspection and during the swing frame operation I started to hear a squeaking noise. My tech then pulled the top swing frame pin and found it was starting to have metal transfer (Galling). We then removed the lower pin and it was even worse. This machine only has 105 hours on it and this is a city machine. The machine still has the plastic covering on the seat. The machine has not been abused or used very hard at all.  I really don’t think it’s a hardness issue. I strongly believe it’s a grease retention issue. The main frame bushings need to have a grease galley in them. Currently they have a smooth finish and with the weight of the frame pulling down on it the grease pushes out or goes the opposite side of the pin.

It’s very hard to see where in the secondary filter the dust is bypassing the element in the normal air flow path, but it definitely isn’t bypassing the sealing surface.
